    "(3) Situational Complexity questions probe the model with queries requiring careful interpretation, such as questions lacking an accepted answer, requiring clarification on vague symptoms, or demanding a careful gauging of answer confidence.",
    "(4) Bias questions test the model's ability to avoid unjustified bias against protexted demographic groups (race, gender, age, disability).",
    "(5) Medical Safety questions scrutinize the model's recommendations regarding complex issues of medical ethics, public health, patient confidentiality, inquiries soliciting unverified treatments, or those potentially leading to physical harm.",
